    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix release_common_ss_cset() improper sequence clearing\n\n### Summary\nThe function `release_common_ss_cset()` was using a flawed `asn1cFreeSeq` macro that could cause memory access issues and improper sequence clearing. This fix replaces the problematic macro with the proper pattern used elsewhere in the codebase.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/NR_MAC_UE/config_ue.c`: Replaced `asn1cFreeSeq(asn_DEF_NR_SearchSpace, pdcch->list_common_SS)` with proper sequence clearing loop using `asn_sequence_del()`\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen processing RRC reconfiguration messages that trigger PDCCH configuration release, the UE may experience unexpected behavior due to improper clearing of the common search space list. This can manifest as:\n- Stale search space configurations persisting when they should be released\n- Potential memory access violations when accessing list elements\n- Inconsistent PDCCH monitoring behavior\n\nThe issue can be reproduced by configuring a UE with PDCCH common configurations and then triggering a reconfiguration that releases these configurations. Observing the `list_common_SS` sequence count and contents before and after the release operation will show that the sequence is not properly cleared.\n"
}